        <div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-4 mb-4"><h3 class="text-sm font-bold mb-2">How does Arizona summer heat affect kitchen suppression systems in Chandler?</h3><p class="text-sm text-gray-600">Arizona's extreme summer heat — Chandler regularly exceeds 110°F — can accelerate degradation of suppression agents, particularly in kitchens that also experience high ambient temperatures from cooking equipment. Arizona Fire Code requires semi-annual NFPA 96 inspections. Schedule one inspection in late summer (August-September) when heat-related degradation is most likely to have occurred.</p></div>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight mb-3 mt-8">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
        <div class="flex flex-col gap-4 mb-8"><div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-4"><h3 class="text-sm font-bold mb-2">Does every Chandler restaurant need a kitchen fire suppression system?</h3><p class="text-sm text-gray-600">Yes. All commercial cooking operations in Chandler producing grease-laden vapors must have an automatic wet chemical suppression system under NFPA 96 and the Arizona Fire Code (IFC-based). This applies to restaurants, bars with food service, hotel kitchens, and corporate cafeterias.</p></div><div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-4"><h3 class="text-sm font-bold mb-2">How often does kitchen fire suppression need to be inspected in Chandler?</h3><p class="text-sm text-gray-600">NFPA 96 requires semi-annual inspection — twice per year — for all commercial kitchen suppression systems. Inspection must be performed by a licensed contractor and documented. The Chandler Fire Department enforces this requirement.</p></div><div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-4"><h3 class="text-sm font-bold mb-2">How much does kitchen suppression inspection cost in Chandler?</h3><p class="text-sm text-gray-600">$170–$380 per system per system. Budget for two inspections annually.</p></div><div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-4"><h3 class="text-sm font-bold mb-2">What is the most common kitchen fire safety violation in Chandler?</h3><p class="text-sm text-gray-600">Common violations in Chandler include: Overdue semi-annual suppression in Downtown Chandler restaurant spaces; Corporate cafeteria suppression on annual rather than semi-annual schedule.</p></div><div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-4"><h3 class="text-sm font-bold mb-2">Who licenses kitchen suppression contractors in AZ?</h3><p class="text-sm text-gray-600">The Arizona State Fire Marshal's Office ((602) 364-1003) licenses fire protection contractors statewide. Verify your suppression contractor holds current AZ credentials before scheduling service.</p></div></div>
